JOHANNESBURG - Fallen Soweto giants Moroka Swallows have suffered a third relegation, falling out of the ABC Motsepe League.The Dube Birds finished second from bottom of the league, collecting only 24 points from 30 fixtures.Swallows were beaten 2-1 by Orange Vaal Professionals on Saturday, which confirmed their relegation.They will now compete in South Africa s fourth tier championship, the SAB League.The once mighty Moroka Swallows won the Nedbank Cup in 2009 and the MTN8 tournament in 2012. Since that last piece of silverware, it has very much been a slippery slope for theBirds who have now suffered a third successive relegation.eNCA